headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard, Portis pace Bucks past Suns 140-129 without Antetokounmpo

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo made a 3-pointer at the buzzer to lift the Miami Heat to a 104-101 win over the Detroit Pistons on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bam Adebayo hits buzzer-beating 3 as the Heat topped the Pistons 104-101

headlines.description: — A floater, a runner, a hook shot, call it whatever.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kyrie Irving's running left-hander at the buzzer lifts Mavs over Nuggets 107-105

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 29 points and the Orlando Magic pulled away from Toronto for a 111-96 victory on Sunday night, handing the Raptors their seventh straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero scores 29 as Magic beat skidding Raptors 111-96

headlines.description: — Sam Hauser had career highs of 30 points and 10 3-pointers to help the short-handed Boston Celtics beat the Washington Wizards 130-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sam Hauser posts career bests of 30 points, 10 3-pointers as Celtics beat Wizards 130-104

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 33 points and 16 rebounds as the San Antonio Spurs overcame 31 points by Brooklyn’s Cam Thomas and beat the Nets 122-115 in overtime Sunday night to snap a three-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama's 33 points, 16 rebounds power the Spurs past Nets 122-115 in overtime

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored 21 points, De’Andre Hunter added 20 and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Los Angeles Clippers 110-93 on Sunday night to snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dejounte Murray, De'Andre Hunter help Hawks beat Clippers 110-93 to snap 3-game skid
